ts against values known from\nexperiments or DFT calculations ({\\beta}- eucrypite). The ReaxFF potential\nreported here can also describe well single-species systems (e.g., Li-metal,\nAl-metal, and condensed phases of silicon), which makes it suitable for\ninvestigating struc- ture and properties of suboxides, atomic-scale mechanisms\nresponsible for phase transformations, as well as oxidation-reduction\nreactions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 16 Jun 2011 21:55:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-05-15"}
